_meanings:
{@--1@} To go beyond,
pass on, over or beyond, cross (time or
space); {#stokamaMtaramatItya#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>;  
{#javAdatIye himavAnaDomuKEH#} <ls>Ki. 14. 54</ls> was
gone to or reached; {#sTAtavyaM te#} 
{#nayanavizayaM yAvadatyeti BAnuH#} <ls>Me. 34</ls> passes
out of sight; {#atItyEkAdaSAhaM tu nAmakarma#}
{#taTA'karot#} <ls>Rām.</ls> after 11 days;  
{#gfhapaMktayaSciramatIyire janEH#} <ls>Śi. 13. 53.</ls>

{@--2@} To enter, step over; {#advAreRa#}
{#ca nAtIyAt grAmaM vA veSma vA vftaM#}
<ls>Ms. 4. 73.</ls>

{@--3@} To excel, surpass, 
outstrip, be more than a match for;  
{#trisrotasaH kAMtimatItya tasTO#} <ls>Ku. 7. 15</ls>;  
{#satyamatItya harito harIMSca vartaMte vAjinaH#} <ls>Ś. 1</ls>;
{#agnistvizA nAtyeti pUzaRaM#} <ls>Śi. 2. 23</ls>;
to exceed, go beyond, transcend;
{#kusIdavfdDirdvEguRyaM nAtyeti#} <ls>Ms. 8. 151</ls> does
not exceed; {#atItya vAcAM manasAM ca#}
{#gocaraM sTitAya#} <ls>Ki. 18. 41</ls>, <ls>Śi. 16. 48.</ls>

{@--4@}
To overcome, subdue, vanquish,
get the better of; {#na pradIpa iva#} 
{#vAyumatyagAt#} <ls>R. 19. 53</ls> did not overcome,
outlive or survive; to overtake,
out-do.

{@--5@} To walk by, walk past,
pass by, leave behind; {#srotovahAM paTi#}
{#nikAmajalAmatItya#} <ls>Ś. 6. 16</ls>; {#sotyagAt#}
{#ASramaM#} <ls>R. 15. 37.</ls>

{@--6@} To omit, neglect,
disregard, violate, transgress, overstep;
{#na dizwamarTamatyetumISo martyaH kaTaMcana#} <ls>Mb.</ls>
avoid; {#atItya hi guRAn sarvAn svaBAvo#}
{#mUrDni vartate#} <ls>H. 1. 15</ls>; {#deSaM kAlaM ca yo'#} 
{#tIyAt#} <ls>Y. 2. 195</ls>; {#atIyAtsAgaro velAM na#}
{#pratijYAmahaM pituH#} <ls>Rām.</ls>; {#BUtAnyatyeti paMca vE#}
<ls>Ms. 12. 90</ls> oversteps the five
elements ({#mokzaM prApnoti#} <ls>Kull.</ls>); {#atyeti#}
{#tatsarvamidaM viditvA#} <ls>Bg. 8. 28</ls>, <ls n="Bg.">14. 20.</ls>

{@--7@} (Intrans.) To pass, elapse
(time); {#atyeti rajanI yA tu sA na#}
{#pratinivartate#} <ls>Rām.</ls>; {#atIte dakziRAyane#} &c.
